-- Manulife Raises CEO’s Pay 21% to $10 Million as Profit Increases
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 2013-03-22T18:04:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-22/manulife-raises-ceo-s-pay-21-to-10-million-as-profit-increases.html
Manulife Financial Corp. (MFC)  awarded
Chief Executive Officer Donald Guloien C$10.4 million ($10.1
million) in 2012, a 21 percent increase from a year earlier,
after Canada’s largest insurer increased annual profit.  Guloien, 55, was awarded C$8.67 million in 2011, according
to a regulatory filing today by the Toronto-based firm.
Manulife reported 2012 profit of C$1.74 billion, compared with
C$129 million a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
